            , mariner, in the county of Kent, in the parish of St. Vickerey's, being in bodily health of sound memory, and considering the perils and dangers of the seas, and other uncertainties of this transitory life, do provide and declare this to be my last Will and Testament. First, I recommend my soul to God that gave it, and my body I give to the earth, or sea, as shall please God to order it: And my worldly estate I dispose thereof as follows. All that remains, the sums of monies, lands, goods, estates, whatever as shall be in any wise owing to me at the time of my decease, I devise the same to my worthy friend, 
